snippet.textDisplay:
I'm sorry but cheating is absolutely disgusting, toxic and shitty, with NO good reasons to justify it. Period.
Being cheated on (and unfortunately I'm talking from experience) can leave someone completely and utterly broken, not 'broken' as in "slightly heartbroken" but broken to their core. They'll never be the same again. The way they think and feel about all relationships and love from then on will change. That betrayal will flip their world upside down. Trust me.
If you're considering cheating, pause your life and look at the reasons why. Talk to your partner and fix things, or end things. It's as simple as that. Don't put someone through the pain.

I'm really surprised by these responses... I've been cheated on but I didn't take any of these people to be like proud of themselves or anything. It's nice hearing the range in opinions and seeing different peoples reasonings and how some of them worked successfully or unsuccessfully on their relationships after.

It's hard getting over being hurt by someone in this way, but seeing the other side has been quite positive for me.

snippet.textDisplay:
None of these people are married. Get cheated on by someone who slept with a married person, a classmate of yours.. and someone who was enlisted in the military and your significant other travels to them to sleep with them all within a 2 month period. Let's see how much trust you'd have then.

To say I loved that person was undeniable.. However, whenever she told me that she slept with a married man.. instantaneously, all of my love for her left and I developed hate, depression, and suicidal tendencies. I've rehabilitated and got what help I've needed but I 100% agree that if you TRULY love someone, you care so much about that person's well-being that cheating isn't even an option.
